        <p class="bk-blurb-lead">What if the Book of Revelation was never meant to predict the future — but to put the Church on trial for abandoning the covenant?</p>
        <p>For generations modern Christianity has turned Revelation into a roadmap of end-times prophecy — raptures, tribulations, and timelines. But the case was filed in the Old Testament. The prophets argued it for centuries. Revelation closed it. And the Church missed every hearing.</p>
        <p>Every verse is drawn directly from Old Testament Scripture — nothing is left to man's imagination. Every seal, every trumpet, every bowl has a root. This is not interpretation. This is excavation.</p>
        <p>This is not another end-times book. This is a covenant lawsuit. Yahuah is the Judge, the Torah is the standard, and Revelation is the verdict. If you have ever felt that something was missing from what you were taught — you were right. Court is now in session.</p>
      </section>

